<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861222-0119 </DOCNO><HL> Sudbury Holdings Buys Firm</HL><DD> 12/22/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SUDSTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sudbury Holdings Inc. said it acquired E-W Mold andamp; Tool Co., Indianapolis, for cash and convertible preferred stock. Terms weren't disclosed.    E-W Mold andamp; Tool is a closely held maker of plastic molds for the electronic, appliance and automotive industries. It has annual sales of about $8 million. Sudbury makes industrial products. </TEXT></DOC>